<br>
That said, if you tend to solo a lot, MA is the way to go.  Fixers can solo fine, but MAs are the best solo class in the game.  With their terrific damage and decent heals, they can cruise through missions like nobody else.  As an added bonus, MAs are extremely desirable in teams due to their excellent damage.<br>
<br>
Fixers can solo pretty well with their news stacking HoTs, but the lack of a direct heal and slightly lower damage output (on average) makes them a tad slower at soloing.  They are extremely useful in teams, and as long as you can get some of the new NCU and HoT buffs, you'll be VERY welcome when teaming.  I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> always</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want a Fixer in the group when I team.<br>
<br>
So if you are torn between the two, I would also have to recommend trying both, and seeing which one you ultimately prefer. One of the best features of AO is its replay value with 12 fairly different professions to choose from.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
