<br>
Case in point: I was playing my 1he ENF (byom/rider) in a team mission with a friend. My doc had to go afk for a little bit, so...of course, had to go attack something anyway. Very orange (almost red) mob + layers + rage + FoB = very dead mob with 90% health remaining (mongo running but not refreshed). My ENF is pretty buff, but not really twinked out to any degree (well, to some degree, but nothing really ridiculous).<br>
<br>
Additionally, with 14.6, ENF will be heavily upgraded. The new buffs in addition to new weapons will make an already strong class very powerful indeed. Worth a look if you're looking for something new.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucrimhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crimhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#660000>(10/21/02 8:01:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2134.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MA/Fixer</span><hr size=1> I'm enjoying both my Fixer and enforcer alts immencely (sp), although I tend towards the Fixer. MA is still king of solo in my opinion. Not too shabby in groups either.<br>
